Privacy Policy

Last updated: June 2026

VineLog ("the App") is designed to help users manage vineyard activities and records.

Information Collection and Use

The App stores vineyard-related data locally on your device, including parcels, activities, statistics, and other records entered by the user.

The App does not require user registration and does not collect personally identifiable information directly.

Analytics and Crash Reporting

The App uses Google Firebase services:

• Firebase Analytics
  Used to understand how the App is used and to improve user experience.

• Firebase Crashlytics
  Used to collect crash reports and technical diagnostics in order to identify and fix application issues.

These services may collect device information, app usage information, and technical diagnostics according to Google's privacy practices.

For more information, please refer to Google's Privacy Policy:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

Location Information

The App may access the device's approximate or precise location, with the user's permission, in order to provide location-based weather information relevant to vineyard management.

Location data is only accessed when required for weather-related features and is not used to identify users.

Photos and Storage

If the user chooses to attach photos to activities, the App may access device photos or storage with the user's permission.

All photos remain under the user's control and are stored locally on the device unless future cloud features are introduced.

Notifications

The App may request permission to send notifications related to vineyard tasks, reminders, and seasonal recommendations.

Users can disable notifications at any time through their device settings.

Data Sharing

The App does not sell, rent, or share personal information with third parties.

Data Security

User-generated vineyard data is stored locally on the device.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be published through an updated version of this document.

